results.name: Triangle of the Multiset Transform of the Fibonacci Sequence.
comment: Short definition of the Multiset Transformation: supposed we have F(w) distinct objects of weight w.  Then T(n,k) is the number of bags of objects with total weight n containing k objects. Multisets means that objects may appear more than once in the bag, but the order of the objects in the bag does not matter.
Apparently A200544 is the limit of the reversed rows as n approaches infinity.
link: Index to Sequence pairs related by Multiset transformations
example: The triangle starts with rows n>=1 and columns k>=1:
xref: Cf. A000045 (column k=1), A089098 (column k=2), A166861 (row sums), A200544 (limiting row?).
